          ? `${stateData.name} has no state sales tax, making tax collection simpler for your Shopify store. You may still need to collect taxes in other states where you have nexus.`
          : `${stateData.name}'s ${stateData.taxRate}% state sales tax rate applies to most physical goods sold to ${stateData.name} customers. Shopify Tax automatically handles ${stateData.name} tax collection and filing. Note that shipping charges are ${stateData.taxRate > 5 ? 'taxable in most cases' : 'sometimes taxable'} in ${stateData.name}.`
        }</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ section -->
  <div class="max-w-3xl mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions — Shipping from {stateData.name}</h2>
    <div class="space-y-5">
      <div class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-2">What is the cheapest way to ship a package from {stateData.name}?</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">For packages under 1 lb, USPS Ground Advantage is typically the cheapest at $<span>{(repRate ?? 5.49).toFixed(2)}</span>–$11.50 depending on destination. For heavier packages going to nearby {regionLabel} states (Zone {selfZone}), compare USPS and UPS — both are competitive. Use the calculator above to find the cheapest rate for your specific weight and destination.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-2">How much does it cost to ship from {stateData.name} to California?</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Shipping from {stateData.name} to California costs approximately ${getRate(uspsGA, 16, ZONE_MATRIX[originRegion]['west'])?.toFixed(2)} (1 lb, USPS Ground Advantage), ${getRate(upsG, 16, ZONE_MATRIX[originRegion]['west'])?.toFixed(2) ?? 'varies'} (UPS Ground), or ${getRate(uspsPM, 16, ZONE_MATRIX[originRegion]['west'])?.toFixed(2)} (USPS Priority Mail, 1–3 days). California falls in Zone {ZONE_MATRIX[originRegion]['west']} from {stateData.name}.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-2">Does {stateData.name} sales tax apply to Shopify shipping charges?</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">{stateData.taxRate === 0 ? `${stateData.name} has no state sales tax — one of only a few US states. This simplifies tax for Shopify merchants shipping from ${stateData.abbr}.` : `${stateData.name}'s ${stateData.taxRate}% state sales tax may apply to shipping charges depending on the product type. Shopify Tax handles this automatically.`}</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-2">How do USPS shipping zones work from {stateData.name}?</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">{stateData.name} is in the {regionLabel} region. Shipping within the {regionLabel} region is Zone {selfZone}. Shipping cross-country reaches Zone {Math.max(...Object.values(ZONE_MATRIX[originRegion]))}. Higher zones = longer distances = higher rates. USPS zones 1–8 determine price for all weight-based USPS services.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-2">What is the USPS Ground Advantage rate from {stateData.name} in 2026?</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">USPS Ground Advantage from {stateData.name}: ${getRate(uspsGA, 16, selfZone)?.toFixed(2)} (1 lb, within {regionLabel}), ${getRate(uspsGA, 80, selfZone)?.toFixed(2)} (5 lb, within {regionLabel}), up to ${getRate(uspsGA, 16, Math.max(...Object.values(ZONE_MATRIX[originRegion])))?.toFixed(2)} (1 lb, cross-country). USPS Ground Advantage replaced First Class Package Service and Parcel Select Ground in 2023.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pb-2">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-2">Should I use UPS or FedEx for shipping from {stateData.name}?</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">UPS Ground and FedEx Ground have very similar rates from {stateData.name}. UPS is slightly better for high-volume commercial accounts. FedEx Home Delivery reaches residential addresses on Saturdays at no extra charge. For packages under 1 lb, USPS beats both. Use the calculator above to compare exact rates for your package size.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Shipping content section -->
  <div class="max-w-3xl mb-10 prose dark:prose-invert prose-sm max-w-none">
    <h2>Shipping from {stateData.name} — Complete Guide 2026</h2>
    <p>{stateData.name} ({stateData.abbr}) is located in the {regionLabel} shipping region, which determines your USPS zone for all package shipments. As a Shopify merchant shipping from {stateData.name}, understanding your shipping zones helps you set accurate rates, choose the right carrier, and optimize your free shipping threshold.</p>

    <h3>How to choose the right carrier from {stateData.name}</h3>
    <p><strong>USPS Ground Advantage</strong> is almost always the best choice for packages under 1 lb shipped from {stateData.name}. For 1–3 lb packages going to nearby {regionLabel} states, USPS Ground Advantage and UPS Ground are competitive — compare using our calculator above. For heavier shipments (10+ lb) going cross-country, UPS and FedEx often offer better rates, especially with commercial account discounts.</p>

    <h3>Shopify Shipping discounts from {stateData.name}</h3>
    <p>Shopify merchants get pre-negotiated discounts of up to 88% off USPS retail rates and 77% off UPS retail rates through Shopify Shipping. This makes Shopify Shipping one of the best multi-carrier shipping options for {stateData.name} merchants — no minimum volume required.</p>

    <h3>USPS flat rate boxes from {stateData.name}</h3>
    <p>USPS Priority Mail flat rate boxes ship from {stateData.name} to anywhere in the US for a fixed price regardless of weight: Small Flat Rate Box ($10.60), Medium Flat Rate Box ($17.20), Large Flat Rate Box ($22.00). If your products are dense or heavy, flat rate boxes from {stateData.name} can significantly reduce shipping costs on heavier orders.</p>

    <h3>Dimensional weight pricing from {stateData.name}</h3>
    <p>UPS and FedEx both use dimensional weight (DIM weight) pricing — if your package is large but light, you pay based on its size rather than actual weight. Calculate your DIM weight: <em>L × W × H ÷ 139</em>. USPS does not apply DIM weight pricing for packages under 1 cubic foot, making it a better choice for bulky-but-light items shipped from {stateData.name}.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Nearby states -->
  {nearbyStates.length > 0 && (
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Nearby States — {regionLabel} Region</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        {nearbyStates.map(s => (
          <a href={`/shipping/${s.slug}/`} class="px-3 py-1.5 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg text-sm hover:border-teal-400 hover:text-teal-700 dark:hover:text-teal-400 dark:hover:border-teal-600 transition">
            {s.name} ({s.abbr})
